28/06/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A suspected leader of the outlawed separatist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) was detained in western Romania on Friday (June 26th), local police said. 
The suspect was caught at the Varsand checkpoint at the border with Hungary while hidden in a truck with 11 Turkish citizens. 
Authorities said the man has been under observation by border police and interior ministry intelligence. 
(Mediafax, Ziare, BTA - 26/06/09)
